# Python Cheatsheet

##String Methods and Functions

### Case Converting

|Code Example| Description |
|-----|-----|
|`capitalize()`| Capitalizes the first word|
|`title()`| Capitalizes all the words in a string |


### String Filling

|Code Example| Description |
|-----|-----|
|`str.format()`| unsure |
|`center()`| Centers a word on a fixed length |
|`zfill()`| Adds zeros at beginning of a string to create similar lengths |


### Regex Like Functions and Methods

|Code Example| Description |
|-----|-----|
|`isalnum()`| True if a value is alphanumeric |
|`isalpha()` | matching strings with letters |
|`isdigit()` | matching strings with numbers |
|`isdecimal()`| match a decimal number |
|`isidentifier()`| if an "_" is valid in a string |

